nd execute on a robot, achieving 81% grasp success over 220 trials across five transparent object types in clutter. (Supported by: grasp feature projections and 9 channels, LeNet classifier, training via wrapped-object point clouds mapped to DLV, particle-filter grasp search, and experimental success rates.)"}]}
